@chr-hertel
Yes. The idea is to keep the contract as a flat `$options` array.
Then each providerâ€™s client is responsible for shaping the outgoing request to match its API (e.g. the **Gemini** client already does this by wrapping options into the appropriate structure and lifting special fields to the top level).
